    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Devices in which photographic film is secured before it is attached to a camera or other image-recording device. Their shape and size depend on the format of the film, and normally includes removable dark-slides to reveal the film before exposure, or to protect the film while removing the film holder from the camera.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
